data.text: @gingercaddy I always get the soreness because of my nerve crap anyhow so I expect that.
@gingercaddy Ahhh yeah I think the Moderna one sounds like it is tougher. As long as it isn't a lot of fluish shit or if that only seems to be for the first 24 I'm good with it.
@gingercaddy I'm glad you got it, brother. Continue to be safe.

@anxiety_4_dayz @gingercaddy OK. Yeah that seems like the common response...though my niece (who is auto immune like me) actually felt fluish the next day. 

I thought Pfizer with the 90 below thing was gonna hurt more but maybe the cold numbs the bruising 🤷‍♀️
@LumpyLouish @gingercaddy Moderna. My deltoid was real sore that night so I took some ibuprofen. Have felt fine since. Oh and and I got a bruise from the needle 🙃
@anxiety_4_dayz @gingercaddy If you want to answer :) Sorry I'm just trying to figure out which one has less reactions in case I have a choice.

@anxiety_4_dayz @gingercaddy Pfizer or Moderna?
And how did you feel in the first 24?
@gingercaddy Thanks. Waiting to hear on my dad's too. I'll feel better knowing he is safe from it. Every time I go out I get a little nervous about bringing to him.
@LumpyLouish @gingercaddy I got mine last week and I'm feeling fine. 😎

@gingercaddy @meows4all My niece is on an epi and didn't need (the one who didn't feel good the next day) but I'll make sure they have available for me in case. I don't carry one but I started getting worse breathing issues lately. (Not terrible just not a good as it has been).

@gingercaddy Oh OK. Thank you for your input. I want to check on others who get Pfizer too in case I have a choice months from now when they get around to me (actually I'm high risk so I see my doc March so may be getting then if he has it available).
@meows4all @gingercaddy No you're good. I just like to let people know because I do get nervous and it isn't just silly and def isn't anti-vaxxer shit but you know that so it was for others :)

@meows4all @gingercaddy I just honestly have bad luck with flu shots because of my condition that I am still a little worried. Pneumonia shot went ok but my body can't rid toxins very well so it doesn't like new things introduced. I'll just make sure to have my inhaler and do it at the doctors.

@gingercaddy You feel ok on it? The one niece that got the Moderna felt off for about a day and the other got Pfizer and felt just a sore arm. The first has juvie RA though and they are both nurses in Boston (that's why they got them)
